      <li>interfere with other customers or the integrity or performance of the Service.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Running untrusted or model-generated code inside a sandbox is an intended use of mitos. The
      restrictions above are about how you use the Service overall, not about what runs inside your
      isolated sandboxes, provided that use is lawful and within these terms.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Your sandboxes, and stopping them</h2>
    <p>
      Sandboxes and other resources consume compute for as long as they run. <strong>You are
      responsible for stopping or deleting resources you no longer need.</strong> Usage charges keep
